                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d28">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War 1939/3197: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Thailand</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Chapman</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Bangkok</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-05-21T15:00:00+07:00"
                            >May 21, 1940—3 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received May 21—7:18 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>32. I have just been informed by a source close to the Prince Regent’s family
                    that the German Minister has promised Thailand, presumably under instructions,
                    the provinces of Kedah and Kelantan and large parts of Indo-China if Germany
                    wins the war. No <hi rend="italic">quid pro quo</hi> mentioned.</p>
                <p>This report not confirmed as yet.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Chapman</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
